  {
    "postId": "hash_1525508586",
    "author": "Thought Catalog",
    "authorProfileUrl": "https://www.facebook.com/thoughtcatalog",
    "text": "The scene is from Halt and Catch Fire, AMC\u2019s drama about the 1980s-90s personal computer and internet revolution that aired from 2014 to 2017. AMC used it to promote the premiere of The Audacity, a new darkly comedic tech satire that premiered this month (April 12, 2026) on AMC and AMC+.\nThe Audacity was created by Jonathan Glatzer (Succession, Better Call Saul). Billy Magnussen plays a flailing data-mining tech CEO navigating power, a mental breakdown, and an unorthodox relationship with his therapist. The cast includes Zach Galifianakis, Sarah Goldberg, Lucy Punch, Simon Helberg, and Rob Corddry.\nAMC\u2019s promo framed it as: \u201cAmbition, ego, disruption. Before tonight\u2019s premiere, revisit where the hustle of workplace culture started with Halt and Catch Fire.\u201d\nThe connection between the 2 shows: both are about tech culture\u2019s capacity to reward the people willing to break the rules. Halt and Catch Fire set that story in the 1980s. The Audacity updates it for Silicon Valley in 2026.\nThe Audacity screened at SXSW on March 14, 2026 and has already been renewed for Season 2.",
